}

<section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
        <h1>COOKIE POLICY</h1>
        <p class="lead">Information about cookies used on our website and how to manage your preferences.</p>
        <p class="breadcrumb"><a asp-action="Index">Home</a> / Cookie Policy</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="content-section">
    <div class="container legal-content">
        <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: May 23, 2026</p>

        <partial name="_LegalEntityInfo" />

        <h2>1. What Are Cookies?</h2>
        <p>
            Cookies are small text files stored on your browser or device by the websites you visit.
            On <strong>juniorleaguecup.com</strong>, cookies are used to provide site functionality,
            enhance security, and improve user experience.
        </p>

        <h2>2. Who Uses Cookies</h2>
        <p>
            This website is operated under the Zenit Event brand within the Junior League Cup (JLC) organization.
            Zenit is a brand of ATA Ventures. The data controller for data collected through cookies is
            <strong>ATA VENTURES BİLGİSAYAR MEDYA SANAYİ VE TİCARET LİMİTED ŞİRKETİ</strong>.
            For details on personal data processing, please see our <a asp-action="Kvkk">Privacy Notice (KVKK)</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>3. Types of Cookies Used</h2>

        <h3>3.1. Strictly Necessary Cookies</h3>
        <p>
            Required for core website functions. Session management, security, and form submission validation
            rely on these cookies. The site may not function properly without them.
        </p>

        <h3>3.2. Functional Cookies</h3>
        <p>
            Used to remember your preferences (language, region, etc.) and personalize your experience.
        </p>

        <h3>3.3. Performance and Analytics Cookies</h3>
        <p>
            Help us analyze visitor counts, page views, traffic sources, and usage statistics anonymously or in aggregate
            to improve site performance.
        </p>

        <h3>3.4. Marketing Cookies (if applicable)</h3>
        <p>
            If third-party advertising or social media integrations are introduced in the future,
            related cookies will only be activated with your explicit consent.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Cookie Retention</h2>
        <p>
            Session cookies are deleted when you close your browser. Persistent cookies may remain on your device
            for a set period (typically 1–12 months), depending on type and purpose.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Managing Cookie Preferences</h2>
        <p>
            You can delete or block cookies through your browser settings. In most browsers, cookie management is available
            under Privacy, Security, or Cookies. Disabling strictly necessary cookies may prevent some features from working.
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Chrome:</strong> Settings → Privacy and security → Cookies</li>
            <li><strong>Firefox:</strong> Settings → Privacy & Security</li>
            <li><strong>Safari:</strong> Preferences → Privacy</li>
            <li><strong>Edge:</strong> Settings → Cookies and site permissions</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>6. Third-Party Cookies</h2>
        <p>
            If external content (video, maps, social media, etc.) is embedded on our site,
            third parties' own cookie policies may apply. We recommend reviewing those platforms' privacy policies separately.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Contact</h2>
        <p>
            For questions about this cookie policy, contact Zenit Event:
            <a href="tel:+902423240354">+90 242 324 03 54</a> ·
            <a href="mailto:info@juniorleaguecup.com">info@juniorleaguecup.com</a>
        </p>

        <div class="legal-related">
            <h3>Related Documents</h3>
            <p>
                <a asp-action="Kvkk">Privacy Notice (KVKK)</a> ·
                <a asp-action="KullanimSartlari">Terms of Use</a> ·
                <a asp-action="Iletisim">Contact</a>
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
